-I'm a cop.
-That's not what I hear.

20:10.710 --> 20:13.042
I'm almost a cop.

20:16.465 --> 20:20.629
-And I'm here to interrogate you.
-Do I look like a rat to you?

20:20.970 --> 20:24.713
Ain't nobody asking nobody
to rat nobody out.

20:26.559 --> 20:28.049
I just--

20:28.728 --> 20:30.719
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:30.980 --> 20:33.972
-Could you stop pacing like that?
-No.

20:34.817 --> 20:37.149
Look, man,
all I wanna know about is Crystal.

20:39.697 --> 20:40.732
My cousin?

20:41.866 --> 20:43.731
She's your cousin?

20:44.285 --> 20:46.651
Then you know who
that asshole she's living with is.

20:46.829 --> 20:48.365
That asshole is my--

20:50.916 --> 20:52.326
Oh, you're smart.

20:52.960 --> 20:54.700
Well, I ain't saying another word.

20:57.506 --> 20:59.246
Listen, T-Dub.

20:59.425 --> 21:00.961
I don't know Crystal very well...

21:01.135 --> 21:05.424
...but the little bit I do know her tells me
she is a good person in a bad situation.

21:07.641 --> 21:10.849
And I think She deserves better,
don't you?

21:11.020 --> 21:14.729
I mean, you're family.

21:18.861 --> 21:21.273
I'm gonna tell you
what you wanna know.

21:22.573 --> 21:25.690
But you have got to bring me some meth.

21:25.868 --> 21:27.699
What the fuck? I can't do that, man.

21:27.870 --> 21:30.111
I've been in here without it
for almost a week...

21:30.289 --> 21:34.248
-...and I cannot fucking take it no more.
ANDY: What the hell, Stackhouse?

21:34.418 --> 21:37.956
-You ain't supposed to be back here.
-We|l, I'm just sweeping, you know?

21:38.130 --> 21:40.712
Yeah? Where's your broom?

21:41.050 --> 21:42.256
That's a good point.

21:42.426 --> 21:45.008
Those squad cars need washing again.

21:45.179 --> 21:46.840
I'm on it, boss.

21:50.226 --> 21:54.219
Shit. Jason-fucking-Stackhouse.
What the fuck am I gonna do?

21:54.396 --> 21:55.977
My heart bleeds for you.

21:56.690 --> 21:59.067
Why don't you do what you do best
and shut up?

22:15.918 --> 22:17.454
I'll be quick.

22:17.753 --> 22:20.244
Cool. I'm just gonna check on Sook.

22:24.885 --> 22:26.421
Hey, Sook.

22:31.809 --> 22:34.016
Sook, you all right back there?

22:37.231 --> 22:39.893
-Shit.
-She ain't answering?

22:40.943 --> 22:41.978
[ZIPPER ZIPS]

22:42.152 --> 22:43.938
Hey. It's still light out.

22:44.113 --> 22:46.695
-You open that, you're gonna--
-You think I give a fuck?

22:48.158 --> 22:49.614
[BILL GRUNTS]

22:55.374 --> 22:57.285
-What happened?
TARA: You're fucking asking me?

22:57.459 --> 22:58.710
ALCIDE:
Have to get her to a hospital.

22:58.878 --> 22:59.867
[TARA GRUNTS]

23:00.045 --> 23:01.034
TARA: Get out.
BILL: But I can help.

23:01.213 --> 23:02.202
Get out!

23:03.299 --> 23:04.630
[GRUNTS]

23:06.510 --> 23:08.296
Don't you fucking die on me, Sookie.

23:09.305 --> 23:11.136
Do not fucking die.

23:13.392 --> 23:15.132
[GRUNTING]

23:15.519 --> 23:16.929
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

23:17.730 --> 23:19.971
[ENGINE STARTS]

23:26.363 --> 23:27.694
Damn.

23:30.868 --> 23:33.075
Boy, you look mean.

23:33.245 --> 23:35.577
You sure do mind good.

23:35.748 --> 23:37.659
You're gonna roll right onto your back...

23:37.833 --> 23:41.621
...and take it like a little girl later on,
ain't you? Heh, heh.

23:41.837 --> 23:43.919
I'm betting against you.

23:47.801 --> 23:48.836
All right, then.

23:49.011 --> 23:50.000
[SAM SHIFTS]

23:50.179 --> 23:51.168
Slide on in here, teddy bear.

23:51.347 --> 23:52.757
What the hell?

23:53.015 --> 23:54.676
[BOBBY GRUNTS]

23:54.850 --> 23:56.386
[BELL RINGS]

23:56.560 --> 23:58.391
[CROWD CHATTERING AND CHEERING]

24:02.691 --> 24:04.397
WOMAN [OVER PA]:
Doctor Seku/er to the ER.

24:04.568 --> 24:05.603
NURSE 1:
All right, let's go.

24:06.946 --> 24:09.858
NURSE 2: All right, BP's dropping.
She's gonna palp, let's go.

24:10.699 --> 24:12.109
NURSE 3:
I'm sorry.

24:14.161 --> 24:15.867
WOMAN 1 :
Get ready to transfuse.

24:21.669 --> 24:23.250
WOMAN 2:
Pressure's steady.

24:25.798 --> 24:27.129
MAN:
Two more.

24:28.384 --> 24:30.090
WOMAN 2:
Line is in.

24:31.553 --> 24:32.838
Here we go.

24:33.722 --> 24:35.053
WOMAN 1:
Piggy-back it.

24:37.226 --> 24:39.638
WOMAN 2: Pressure's good.
All right, I'll call the blood bank.

24:39.812 --> 24:43.396
Another four units on standby,
just in case we need it.

24:43.565 --> 24:46.728
-She's starting to seize.
MAN: Okay, got it.

24:47.319 --> 24:50.231
WOMAN 1: Pressure's accelerating.
WOMAN 2: All right, let's get the cart in here.

24:50.406 --> 24:51.566
MAN:
Watch that line.

24:53.200 --> 24:55.065
[MACHINE BEEPING]

24:58.205 --> 25:01.789
DOCTOR: Miss Thornton?
-How is she?

25:03.085 --> 25:05.747
-She's lost a lot of blood.
-How much blood?

25:05.921 --> 25:08.412
-A lot.
-Oh, my God.

25:09.049 --> 25:10.914
What about a transfusion?
I mean, can't--

25:11.093 --> 25:12.754
We tried. Her body rejected it.

25:12.928 --> 25:14.668
Maybe you gave
the wrong kind of blood?

25:14.847 --> 25:17.839
You checked her first?
You better not have taken a fucking guess.

25:18.267 --> 25:20.132
Your friend doesn't have a blood type.

25:20.978 --> 25:22.684
-What?
-Everybody has a blood type.

25:22.855 --> 25:24.220
Exactly.

25:24.565 --> 25:27.102
But for whatever reason,
we couldn't establish hers...

25:27.276 --> 25:31.690
...and we are running out of time.
So I put in an order for O-negative.

25:31.864 --> 25:34.150
O-neg is universal donor.

25:34.700 --> 25:35.735
But your friend....

25:35.909 --> 25:37.240
[DOCTOR SIGHS]

25:37.411 --> 25:39.948
I have never seen a reaction
like that before.

25:41.999 --> 25:43.114
I'm sorry.

25:44.960 --> 25:47.827
I'm afraid you're gonna
have to notify the family.

25:48.714 --> 25:49.703
[GUNSHOT]
[DOG YELPS]

25:50.340 --> 25:53.582
MAN 1:
Piece of shit. Don't even die good.

25:53.761 --> 25:55.297
Bring in the next one.

25:55.471 --> 25:57.462
[CHATTERING]

25:59.349 --> 26:01.476
Tommy, Mama loves you.

26:04.396 --> 26:05.852
[BARKS]

26:06.982 --> 26:08.483
JOE LEE:
Get up, boy.

26:09.568 --> 26:11.684
[BOTH BARKING]

26:12.488 --> 26:14.604
MAN 2:
He's gonna bring me some money.

26:14.823 --> 26:17.280
[BOTH GROWLING]

26:20.996 --> 26:22.497
MAN 3:
Fifty dollar riding.

26:29.671 --> 26:30.706
[BELL RINGS]

26:30.881 --> 26:32.166
[CROWD CHEERING]

26:35.385 --> 26:37.512
MELINDA: Go, Tommy.
-Take it to him, Tommy.

26:37.971 --> 26:39.507
Oh, boy.

26:39.681 --> 26:41.842
[ALARM WAILING]

26:42.017 --> 26:43.518
MAN 4:
Motherfucker.

26:44.686 --> 26:46.768
SAM:
Git. Go. Git.

26:46.939 --> 26:49.681
-Come on, Tommy.
JOE LEE: Tommy, get out of there.

26:51.735 --> 26:53.851
SAM:
Go on, git. Get out of here.

26:54.363 --> 26:56.194
Go, go, go.

26:57.533 --> 27:00.240
MAN 5: Hey, you owe me 500 bucks.
MAN 6: I don't owe you shit, boy.

27:00.410 --> 27:01.946
SAM:
Hey.

27:03.330 --> 27:04.365
Hey, son.

27:04.540 --> 27:06.701
[DOG GROWLING]

27:07.334 --> 27:08.870
[BARKS]

27:09.044 --> 27:10.705
Don't you snarl at me.

27:11.547 --> 27:12.536
[WHIMPERS]

27:12.714 --> 27:13.920
Good dog.

27:14.258 --> 27:15.247
Good, good.

27:15.425 --> 27:17.040
Now get the fuck out of here.

27:19.388 --> 27:20.878
[TOMMY SHIFTS]

27:25.269 --> 27:26.304
Give him your clothes.

27:26.478 --> 27:28.935
-Don't you tell--
-Give him your clothes.

27:32.693 --> 27:34.684
[PANTING]

27:35.988 --> 27:38.479
Sorry. Hey, hey, Lafayette.

27:38.657 --> 27:40.238
You got a minute?

27:42.161 --> 27:45.403
Last time you came to me all shaky
like this, you wanted to buy some V.

27:45.747 --> 27:48.739
Oh, no. I told you, that shit's behind me.
I just need some meth.

27:49.418 --> 27:52.410
-What?
-We|l, it ain't for me, I swear.

27:52.588 --> 27:55.250
It's for this dude who we got in lockup.

27:55.424 --> 28:00.009
He's got this information I need, but he'll
only give it to me if I get him some meth.

28:00.179 --> 28:04.172
Jason, no. I don't deal no fucking meth.

28:04.433 --> 28:06.765
And even if I did,
I wouldn't sell the shit to you.

28:06.935 --> 28:08.596
And you ought to thank me for it.

28:09.563 --> 28:11.519
Goddamn it, Lafayette, I'm in love.

28:12.941 --> 28:14.147
With the dude in jail?

28:14.318 --> 28:15.353
[PHONE BUZZING]

28:15.527 --> 28:17.563
No. With his cousin.

28:19.948 --> 28:22.064
-He|lo?
TARA: It's me.

28:22.242 --> 28:24.449
-Tara?
-You found her? Where's she at?

28:24.620 --> 28:27.202
-|t's Sookie.
-What about her?

28:29.791 --> 28:31.247
Tara?

28:31.710 --> 28:33.826
Say something.
You're starting to freak me out.

28:34.171 --> 28:37.129
We're at the hospital in Ruston.

28:38.675 --> 28:40.666
Sook’s in a coma, Jason.

28:40.844 --> 28:42.550
You need to get here.

28:42.721 --> 28:44.552
You need to get here now.

28:45.057 --> 28:46.593
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

28:47.267 --> 28:50.134
Sook's in the hospital.
Sook's in the fucking hospital.

28:50.312 --> 28:52.303
-You warm now, son?
-Little better, yeah.

28:52.481 --> 28:54.312
SAM:
Well, now you give a shit.

28:54.483 --> 28:57.316
I thought Tara had a Shitty mother,
but you take the cake.

28:57.486 --> 29:00.819
-Don't talk to your mother that way.
-Don't fucking talk to me that way.

29:00.989 --> 29:03.901
You like making people scared?
Think you're good at it?

29:04.076 --> 29:08.035
I can't understand the power you got over
them, because I see you for what you are.

29:08.205 --> 29:10.662
You're just a scared man
in saggy underpants...

29:10.832 --> 29:13.869
...with no discernable life skills
whatsoever.

29:15.504 --> 29:17.335
-Come on, Tommy.
-Where you going?

29:17.506 --> 29:19.542
-Taking him with me.
-What? I can't.

29:19.716 --> 29:21.707
You can, Tommy.
You can be free of them.

29:21.885 --> 29:23.000
He's my son.

29:23.178 --> 29:26.170
-You can't do this to me.
-Oh, yes, I can, and so can he.

29:26.723 --> 29:29.760
I thought the Merlottes
were the worst people I'd ever met.

29:29.935 --> 29:32.847
The two of you Mickens make them
look like a couple Dalai Lamas.

29:33.021 --> 29:34.477
You really fucking do.

29:34.648 --> 29:36.513
I'm sorry, Sam. I know we let you down--

29:36.692 --> 29:38.432
SAM:
You're sorry. Great.

29:38.777 --> 29:40.688
Duly noted. Come on, Tommy.

29:41.196 --> 29:42.231
You coming with me?

29:45.867 --> 29:50.110
Tommy, I can't promise you
a perfect life...

29:50.289 --> 29:53.326
...but I can promise you
it'll be better than this one.

29:56.461 --> 29:59.544
-Yeah, I'm coming.
SAM: All right.

30:00.132 --> 30:02.043
Come on, let's do this.

30:03.677 --> 30:05.713
Don't you worry, Lindy.

30:06.221 --> 30:08.303
-We'll get him back.
-I hate you.

30:08.473 --> 30:11.055
I hate your fucking guts.

30:11.601 --> 30:12.807
[MELINDA SOBBING]

30:14.563 --> 30:17.726
I understand that this is hard,
but as the responsible party here...

30:17.899 --> 30:20.561
...there's certain decisions
that you might have to make.

30:20.736 --> 30:22.476
No. No. I ain't responsible.

30:22.654 --> 30:24.235
But you are the next of kin.

30:26.158 --> 30:27.193
[SIGHS]

30:27.367 --> 30:29.858
Maybe, but I ain't responsible.

30:30.037 --> 30:31.902
I mean, I can't be.

30:32.080 --> 30:34.913
I understand your position,
but in the event your sister--

30:35.083 --> 30:36.414
Just leave him alone, please.

30:36.585 --> 30:38.621
-But I--
-I said, leave him alone.

30:39.338 --> 30:42.455
Go find somebody else's organs
to harvest or some Shit like that.

30:42.632 --> 30:43.792
I'm sorry.

30:44.551 --> 30:46.587
I'll smooth it over.

30:47.304 --> 30:48.544
Thank you.

30:48.722 --> 30:50.929
Listen to me. Fuck her.
This shit ain't over.

30:51.099 --> 30:52.088
[JASON SIGHS]

30:52.267 --> 30:54.349
TARA:
Just don't make no sense.

30:54.519 --> 30:57.261
How can Sookie not have a blood type?

30:58.190 --> 30:59.771
You got one?

31:00.400 --> 31:01.776
AB-negative.

31:02.319 --> 31:04.981
I only know it because
I'm always cutting myself...

31:05.155 --> 31:07.612
...with power tools and whatnot.

31:07.991 --> 31:10.778
But Sook,
she ain't never really been sick before.

31:10.952 --> 31:12.943
Definitely never stayed in a hospital.

31:13.330 --> 31:14.615
Wasn't even born in one.

31:16.041 --> 31:17.281
I didn't know that.

31:18.043 --> 31:22.036
Yeah, our mama was always waiting
till the last minute to do everything. Heh.

31:22.464 --> 31:27.254
And Sook, she was coming out real fast,
so there wasn't any time.

31:27.427 --> 31:30.214
Our daddy had to deliver her
on the dining-room table.

31:32.307 --> 31:34.468
Saw more of it than I cared to.

31:40.649 --> 31:44.016
You think it's all this vampire blood
she's had that did this to her?

31:44.194 --> 31:46.856
It ain't the blood she drank that did this.

31:47.030 --> 31:50.238
It's the piece-of—shit vampire
she drank it from.

31:52.744 --> 31:55.861
-You really kicked him out in the sun?
-Mm-hm.

31:56.039 --> 32:00.578
And he's nothing but fucking ash now,
and good riddance.

32:04.464 --> 32:06.796
Hey, Sook.

32:07.551 --> 32:09.382
Don't you do this to me.

32:14.349 --> 32:18.262
I wasn't playing before
when I said you're all I got.

32:19.354 --> 32:22.642
I fucking need you. So come on back.

32:25.235 --> 32:26.771
And I fucking need you too.

32:27.028 --> 32:28.689
Come on, y'all. Stop cussing at her.

32:29.865 --> 32:33.073
We're gonna figure this thing out.

32:41.334 --> 32:43.325
[BIRD CHIRPING]

32:46.673 --> 32:48.334
[WOMEN GIGGLING]

33:29.007 --> 33:30.872
SOOKIE:
Where am I?

33:31.593 --> 33:33.049
WOMAN:
SooMe.

33:34.596 --> 33:36.086
You're in the hospital.

33:36.264 --> 33:38.425
You can't seem to stay out of trouble,
can you?

33:38.600 --> 33:41.091
I don't-- Do you know me?

33:41.269 --> 33:43.351
-Come.
-Who are you?

33:43.522 --> 33:45.103
I'm Claudine.

33:46.024 --> 33:48.185
Oh, dear. Your cup is empty.

33:49.402 --> 33:51.358
We can't have that, can we?

34:15.178 --> 34:17.840
SOOKIE:
Oh, Claudine.

34:18.306 --> 34:20.137
I know. It's beautiful.

34:20.850 --> 34:22.226
Drink.

34:27.649 --> 34:28.638
My God.

34:29.985 --> 34:32.146
It's the most amazing thing
I've ever tasted.

34:32.320 --> 34:33.651
You've had it before.

34:47.460 --> 34:49.371
Okay, but where did she come from?

34:49.546 --> 34:50.831
Don't be fooled.

34:51.006 --> 34:54.214
That pond is bigger and deeper
than you think.

34:56.845 --> 34:58.210
Can we dance?

34:58.763 --> 35:00.503
We can always dance.

35:01.099 --> 35:05.183
-I knew you were gonna say that.
-And I knew you were going to say that.

35:05.353 --> 35:06.342
Come.

35:06.521 --> 35:07.852
[SOOKIE GIGGLES]

35:08.023 --> 35:13.518
I think over again my small adventures,
my fears...

35:13.695 --> 35:16.528
...those small ones that seemed so big.

35:16.698 --> 35:19.815
For all the vital things
I had to get and reach...

35:19.993 --> 35:25.113
...and yet there is only one great thing,
the only thing...

35:25.290 --> 35:30.705
...to live to see the great day that dawns
and the light that fills the world.

35:31.880 --> 35:33.165
That's beautiful.

35:33.340 --> 35:35.752
That's because that shit is Inuit.

35:36.635 --> 35:40.127
And we all is used to lesser religions.

35:49.397 --> 35:52.264
I'm gonna have to Sit this one out.

35:52.442 --> 35:55.058
I guess I don't have the endurance
that you all have.

35:55.236 --> 35:57.488
Oh, not to worry. You will one day.

35:57.656 --> 35:59.988
-You promise? Ha, ha.
-I do.

36:00.158 --> 36:01.398
Oh, Sookie.

36:03.495 --> 36:05.577
Don't go back. Come with us.

36:05.747 --> 36:07.703
-Come with you where?
-Our home.

36:07.874 --> 36:10.240
It's more beautiful
than anything you can imagine.

36:10.418 --> 36:12.875
-How do you get there?
-Just swim. Come.

36:13.046 --> 36:16.459
SOOKIE: Hate deep water. Mama and Daddy
were killed by water. Don’t. Can’t swim.

36:16.633 --> 36:18.840
I can't. See, I never learned to swim.

36:19.010 --> 36:22.548
CLA UDINE: Do not fear the water.
It wasn’t the water that killed them.

36:22.722 --> 36:24.098
What?

36:24.849 --> 36:27.807
If it wasn't the water that killed them,
then what did?

36:30.522 --> 36:34.140
The dark approaches.
The dark approaches.

36:35.944 --> 36:38.651
-How is she?
-Motherfucker.

36:39.030 --> 36:40.611
-She's dying.
-Thanks to you.

36:40.782 --> 36:42.647
-I can help.
-The fuck you can.

36:42.826 --> 36:45.784
Aw, hell, no. He's the one who did this.

36:46.413 --> 36:47.994
-Shit.
-Jason, there is no time.

36:48.164 --> 36:50.155
My blood can save her.

36:50.333 --> 36:53.621
CLAUDINE: Hurry. I will see you all at home.
WOMAN: I've never seen a vampire before.

36:53.795 --> 36:56.628
CLAUDINE: I promise. You don't want to.
SOOKIE: Bill's not like that.

36:56.798 --> 36:59.084
CLAUDINE: I don't have the time
to explain why you're wrong.

36:59.259 --> 37:02.171
You have to come with us, Sookie.
It's not safe for you anymore.

37:02.345 --> 37:03.960
-Why?
-He will steal your light.

37:04.139 --> 37:05.970
What light?

37:08.309 --> 37:09.344
-SooHe.
-No.

37:09.519 --> 37:11.475
I'm not going with you.
I don't know you.

37:12.147 --> 37:13.808
Do not let him take it from you.

37:15.066 --> 37:16.727
Promise me.

37:19.154 --> 37:21.486
SOOKIE:
How do I get back from here?

37:24.826 --> 37:26.316
Claudine?

37:27.829 --> 37:29.194
Claudine.

37:40.467 --> 37:41.707
-Do it.
-Jason.

37:41.885 --> 37:44.718
Tara, it's my call.

37:48.057 --> 37:49.342
Do it.

38:12.665 --> 38:14.371
JASON:
Come on, Sookie.

38:33.311 --> 38:35.267
MAGISTER:
I come bearing gifts...

38:36.064 --> 38:39.431
...because I want you to know
how rotten I feel...

38:39.609 --> 38:42.316
...about the way I've been treating you.

38:42.487 --> 38:46.196
I sent one of my minions to Tiffany's...

38:46.908 --> 38:50.571
...to pick up a little something for you.

38:52.163 --> 38:55.405
-How'd you know I was a Tiffany's girl?
-Mm.

38:57.085 --> 38:58.871
Most women are.

38:59.045 --> 39:03.789
And those who aren't
just think they're not.

39:04.592 --> 39:06.093
-They're beautiful.
-Mm.

39:06.761 --> 39:08.342
They're sterling silver.

39:09.973 --> 39:11.713
Excellent.

39:11.891 --> 39:14.348
They'll match my chains.

39:14.602 --> 39:16.593
[MAGISTER CHUCKLES]

39:17.438 --> 39:22.228
Tsk. Unfortunately,
seeing you now I realize...

39:22.819 --> 39:25.151
...your ears are already pierced.

39:28.366 --> 39:31.483
Would you object
to my piercing your eyelids?

39:34.706 --> 39:36.162
Not at all.

39:36.332 --> 39:37.868
Very well.

39:47.969 --> 39:49.800
MAGISTER:
Mm-hm.

39:49.971 --> 39:50.960
[DOOR OPENS]

39:51.222 --> 39:53.304
ERIC: Enough.
-Eric.

39:56.436 --> 39:58.643
Mr. Northman.

39:59.147 --> 40:01.763
It's only enough
if Bill Compton is with you.

40:01.941 --> 40:04.318
-Is he?
ERIC: No, Magister.

40:05.069 --> 40:07.230
But the queen of Louisiana is.

40:08.448 --> 40:09.483
Our deal was--

40:09.657 --> 40:12.820
I'll confess that you were correct before
in suspecting me...

40:13.244 --> 40:17.112
...but everything I did was at her behest.

40:19.500 --> 40:21.991
You realize, of course,
you're committing treason...

40:23.338 --> 40:26.205
...throwing your queen under the bus
as you are.

40:26.382 --> 40:28.998
Oh, but she's no longer my queen.

40:29.177 --> 40:31.668
My loyalty is to Mississippi now.

40:31.846 --> 40:33.347
[DOOR OPENS]

40:33.514 --> 40:37.348
RUSSELL: And Mississippi's proud to claim
Mr. Northman as one of her own.

40:38.394 --> 40:40.510
Love the place. Love your vibe.

40:40.688 --> 40:42.940
We must talk franchising later.

40:44.150 --> 40:45.515
[CHUCKLES]

40:45.693 --> 40:47.069
Russell Edgington.

40:47.236 --> 40:49.363
You may call me King.

40:51.282 --> 40:53.398
IS it true what Northman says?

40:55.328 --> 40:57.114
Yes, Magister.

40:57.288 --> 40:59.574
Then I'm afraid
I'm gonna have to arrest you.

41:01.584 --> 41:03.700
By the powers vested in me
by the authority...

41:03.878 --> 41:05.163
-...I hereby--
RUSSELL: The authority?

41:05.338 --> 41:07.329
[LAUGHS]

41:07.715 --> 41:09.831
Are you serious?

41:10.009 --> 41:12.876
Who are the authority?

41:14.806 --> 41:16.762
What gave them the authority?

41:17.225 --> 41:19.056
Nothing. No one.

41:19.227 --> 41:20.763
You okay?

41:20.937 --> 41:26.273
They took it, as I am taking it today.
I no longer recognize the authority.

41:28.277 --> 41:30.893
You are aware-- She stays on the table.

41:33.783 --> 41:38.868
You are aware that just saying that
is a cardinal Sin.

41:39.455 --> 41:42.413
I am aware ofjust what a tough little boat
I'm putting you in.

41:42.583 --> 41:45.199
Honestly, it is kind of fun.

41:47.422 --> 41:50.755
You know I'm beholden by duty to convey
your blasphemy to the authority--

41:50.925 --> 41:54.588
To the authority?
Well, that won't be happening.

41:54.762 --> 41:56.627
But enough about you.

41:57.306 --> 42:03.097
In exchange for the money she owes
the IRS, Queen Sophie Anne...

42:03.938 --> 42:07.305
...has kindly accepted
my marriage proposal.

42:08.276 --> 42:10.312
I had no choice.

42:12.655 --> 42:15.818
-Your Majesty--
-Yes, my loyal subject?

42:17.785 --> 42:21.903
Oh, we would be delighted
if you would officiate the wedding for us.

42:22.373 --> 42:27.117
I am forbidden to conduct
any rights of alignment...

42:27.295 --> 42:28.785
...unless specifically authori--

42:28.963 --> 42:32.672
Unless specifically authorized
to do so by the authority.

42:32.842 --> 42:36.630
Yes, well, perhaps you have not
quite grasped the subtext...

42:36.804 --> 42:41.719
...of our earlier exchange,
but there's a new fucking authority in town.

42:44.020 --> 42:48.559
I swear fealty now and always
to the one true vampire authority...

42:48.733 --> 42:51.475
...in whose wisdom and justice I--

42:51.986 --> 42:53.317
[GRUNTS]

42:57.992 --> 43:01.200
RUSSELL:
You pathetic fool.

43:01.370 --> 43:06.410
Blindly doing the bidding of others,
just like humans.

43:06.584 --> 43:10.748
It's vampires like you who've been holding
the rest of us back for centuries.

43:40.701 --> 43:42.362
[SCREAMING]

43:44.664 --> 43:46.029
[SCREAMING AND GROANING]

43:47.708 --> 43:50.996
You can dish it out, but you sure
can't take it, can you, Magister?

43:51.170 --> 43:53.547
Let's see how this plays out, Pam.

43:53.714 --> 43:55.045
You can always taunt later.

43:56.801 --> 43:58.632
Can we hurry this along?

43:58.803 --> 44:00.543
I'm getting cold feet.

44:00.721 --> 44:03.133
Of course, my little pudding.

44:05.101 --> 44:10.016
This could be so much less painful
if you just said the fucking words.

44:11.566 --> 44:16.401
I am bound by duty
to uphold the sacred laws of--

44:16.737 --> 44:17.726
[MAGISTER GASPS]

44:17.905 --> 44:20.066
Uh-uh-uh.

44:21.200 --> 44:22.701
Your call.

44:29.750 --> 44:32.366
I hereby pronounce you...

44:33.880 --> 44:35.962
...husband and wife.

44:37.633 --> 44:38.918
Thank you.

44:39.093 --> 44:40.594
Yes, thanks.

44:40.761 --> 44:42.262
So happy I could bleed.

44:43.514 --> 44:45.379
ERIC:
Congratulations, Your Majesties.

44:45.558 --> 44:46.764
Yes, congrats.

44:48.144 --> 44:51.602
You realize, of course,
the authority will never recognize--

44:51.772 --> 44:52.807
Its own irrelevancy?

44:52.982 --> 44:56.770
That's where you and I differ, Magister.
I truly believe they will, and soon.

44:58.613 --> 45:00.274
[SNIFFS]

45:01.449 --> 45:05.283
Andalusia, the Iberian Peninsula.

45:05.953 --> 45:09.616
Mmm. Later 9th century, no?

45:10.583 --> 45:12.289
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

45:12.460 --> 45:14.166
Well, whatever.

45:14.629 --> 45:17.120
It's a long enough time
for you to have outgrown...

45:17.298 --> 45:21.792
...your blind allegiance to the authority
and their rule of law.

45:21.969 --> 45:23.880
There is only one law:

45:24.055 --> 45:27.513
The law of nature,
the survival of the fittest.

45:27.683 --> 45:29.969
We need to take this world back
from the humans...

45:30.144 --> 45:34.478
...not placate them with billboards
and PR campaigns while they destroy it.

45:34.774 --> 45:38.392
That is not authority.
That is abdicating authority.

45:38.569 --> 45:39.979
ERIC:
Your Majesty.

45:41.489 --> 45:42.899
Shall we?

45:44.575 --> 45:45.906
[SIGHS]

45:46.077 --> 45:47.783
We shall.

45:48.579 --> 45:49.819
[GRUNTS]

45:50.456 --> 45:52.412
Actually, no.

45:54.710 --> 45:58.919
Say hello to the true death.
